nl2test_metadata.code: package org.apache.commons.csv; import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals; import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse; import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull; import java.io.IOException; import java.io.Reader; import java.io.StringReader; import java.util.List; import java.util.stream.Collectors; import org.junit.jupiter.params.ParameterizedTest; import org.junit.jupiter.params.provider.ValueSource; public class CsvMaxRowsTest { private void assertRecord(final CSVRecord record, final String... expectedValues) { assertNotNull(record); assertEquals(expectedValues.length, record.size()); for (int i = 0; i < expectedValues.length; i++) { assertEquals(expectedValues[i], record.get(i)); } } @ParameterizedTest @ValueSource(longs = {-1, 0, 1, 2, 3, 9223372036854775807L}) public void testCsvParserMaxRows(long max_row_limit) throws IOException { final String csvString = "A1,A2,A3\nB1,B2,B3\nC1,C2,C3"; final Reader csvReader = new StringReader(csvString); final CSVFormat csvFormat = CSVFormat.DEFAULT.builder().setMaxRows(max_row_limit).build(); try (final CSVParser parser = CSVParser.parse(csvReader, csvFormat)) { final List<CSVRecord> recordList = parser.stream().collect(Collectors.toList()); assertFalse(recordList.isEmpty()); assertRecord(recordList.get(0), "A1", "A2", "A3"); if (max_row_limit <= 0 || max_row_limit > 1) { assertRecord(recordList.get(1), "B1", "B2", "B3"); } if (max_row_limit <= 0 || max_row_limit > 2) { assertRecord(recordList.get(2), "C1", "C2", "C3"); } if (max_row_limit > 0) { long expectedSize = Math.min(3, max_row_limit); assertEquals(expectedSize, recordList.size()); } else { assertEquals(3, recordList.size()); } } } }
